The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Hindustan Copper Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 112.52 crore and a sales turnover of Rs 1,053.52 crore for the financial year 2005-06. According to the provisional results of the company, Hindustan Copper has registered an 88.43 per cent growth in sales turnover and 116.14 per cent growth in net profit over the previous year. During the year, the company has sold 38,788 tonnes of copper, of which 1,402 tonnes were exported.

 TNT India has launched India Road Network, which will link over 140 cities and span across 32,000 km. The network, according to the company, will continue to expand in the future. It will offer customers a door-to-door, day definite solution with track and trace capabilities.

 Ashok Leyland has closed the year 2005-06 with sales of 61,626 vehicles. It represents a 12.6 per cent growth over its2004-05 sales of 54,740 vehicles. Sales in the domestic medium and heavy commercial vehicle segment touched 55,993 vehicles, reflecting a 17.6 per cent growth.

 Kotak Mutual Fund has been given the ?best bond fund group over three years? award at the recently held Lipper India Fund Award 2006. The award was in recognition of the consistent outperformance of schemes.

 Khaitan has bagged the ?mera brand? award for being the most popular fan brand in the country at the third Consumer World Awards held in March this year. The award was instituted by AMGF Intercorp Ltd, a media and brand rating company.

 Aviva Life Insurance has opened 63 branches more, taking the total number to 104 in India. The company has also increased its field force capacity to nearly 9,500 financial planning advisors. 

 Tanla Solution Ltd has reported a consolidated net profit of Rs 30.24 crore on a total income of Rs 63.12 crore for the financial year ended March 31. The company had registered a net profit of Rs 6.84 crore and a net income of Rs 22.72 crore for fiscal 2005.

 Uttam Galva Steels Ltd has increased the prices of its galvanised steel products in the domestic market by Rs 1,000 per tonne. The increase in price will compensate for the input costs. Further price hikes across all categories are also possible.

 Colgate-Palmolive (India) Ltd has launched the Colgate 360 toothbrush. The product has a tongue cleaner located at the back of the brush head and inter dental bristles. The brush is available in four colours and priced at Rs 55.

